See? What did I tell ya?

201
00:06:57,332 --> 00:06:58,774
Weird.

202
00:06:59,718 --> 00:07:02,483
Hi, uh, Penny?
I'm Frankie.

203
00:07:02,600 --> 00:07:04,523
It's my first day. I guess
we're gonna be working together.

204
00:07:04,644 --> 00:07:06,525
Oh, well,
welcome aboard, Frankie.

205
00:07:06,637 --> 00:07:08,115
Oh, you're gonna love
working here.

206
00:07:08,251 --> 00:07:10,551
We like to think of ourselves as a big ol' family.
(Cash register beeping)

207
00:07:10,665 --> 00:07:11,838
(Laughs) Oh, great.

208
00:07:11,972 --> 00:07:14,400
So just picking up
a few things on my break.

209
00:07:14,494 --> 00:07:15,648
I'm getting this
for my daughter.

210
00:07:15,763 --> 00:07:17,047
She loves rainbows.

211
00:07:17,238 --> 00:07:19,601
And my son's been wanting
this clock radio

212
00:07:19,760 --> 00:07:22,045
that projects the time
up onto the ceiling,

213
00:07:22,146 --> 00:07:23,240
'cause I guess it's too much

214
00:07:23,349 --> 00:07:25,244
to roll over
and see that it's noon.

215
00:07:25,377 --> 00:07:26,634
(Laughs) Right.

216
00:07:26,836 --> 00:07:29,873
All right.
Okay, that's $78.96.

217
00:07:29,974 --> 00:07:32,183
Ooh, hold on. I think
you forgot my employee discount.

218
00:07:32,320 --> 00:07:34,777
Oh, yeah, that doesn't
kick in for 20 days.

219
00:07:35,003 --> 00:07:36,551
20 days?

220
00:07:36,795 --> 00:07:39,472
That's all the way
up to... Christmas Eve.

221
00:07:39,585 --> 00:07:40,730
Yeah, I know.

222
00:07:40,849 --> 00:07:42,172
See, people used to
take these jobs

223
00:07:42,288 --> 00:07:43,676
