I'll keep you posted. (Beep)</i>

248
00:08:41,058 --> 00:08:42,519
What are you doing?

249
00:08:42,717 --> 00:08:44,233
Chillin' in my new crib.

250
00:08:44,514 --> 00:08:46,556
Your "crib" is full
of stolen furniture.

251
00:08:46,675 --> 00:08:47,921
Hey! It's not stolen,

252
00:08:48,033 --> 00:08:49,404
'cause Uncle Rusty
called acey deucey.

253
00:08:49,535 --> 00:08:50,877
Now could you close
the door, please?

254
00:08:50,974 --> 00:08:52,531
I'm not paying
to heat the world.

255
00:08:54,552 --> 00:08:57,134
<i>Well, the days until Christmas</i>
<i>were going by fast,</i>

256
00:08:57,280 --> 00:08:59,481
<i>and so were all</i>
<i>my Christmas presents.</i>

257
00:08:59,596 --> 00:09:02,041
I'm not sure about the size,
but this is the only one left.

258
00:09:02,192 --> 00:09:03,305
How do I look?

259
00:09:03,423 --> 00:09:05,984
Fat.
I mean, you're not fat.

260
00:09:06,110 --> 00:09:07,542
The sweatshirt
makes you <i>look</i> fat.

261
00:09:07,664 --> 00:09:10,720
And that rainbow pattern?
A little young for you.

262
00:09:10,872 --> 00:09:12,768
It is a little young for me.

263
00:09:12,948 --> 00:09:14,902
I'll get it for my niece.

264
00:09:15,655 --> 00:09:17,910
Ooh, a clock radio.

265
00:09:19,081 --> 00:09:22,065
<i>My hopes of a discount</i>
<i>Christmas were fading fast.</i>

266
00:09:22,188 --> 00:09:23,778
<i>All I wanted to do</i>
<i>was kick up my feet</i>

267
00:09:23,903 --> 00:09:25,554
<i>with a can of frosting.</i>

268
00:09:25,920 --> 00:09:28,823
<i>But Sue had already used up all my
cabinet frosting.</i> (Packaging rustles)

269
00:09:29,040 --> 00:09:31,840
<i>So I had to go deep</i>
<i>into my reserves.</i>

270
00:09:35,119 --> 00:09:36,701
(Scoffs) Seriously?

271
00:09:36,939 --> 00:09:38,564
Coming together, right?

272
00:09:38,680 --> 00:09:41,029
Masculine,
yet with a touch of whimsy.

273
00:09:42,402 --> 00:09:44,313
Oh, uh, your frosting's
not there.

274
00:09:44,462 --> 00:09:46,021
I put that and your other stuff
in the back,

275
00:09:46,137 --> 00:09:48,029
'cause it was an eyesore.

276
00:09:48,290 --> 00:09:50,837
Oh, and, uh, instead of
a new amp for Christmas,

277
00:09:50,968 --> 00:09:52,169
I'd like an accent rug.

278
00:09:52,290 --> 00:09:54,925
You know, really help
define the space.

279
00:09:55,048 --> 00:09:56,208
Yeah, well,
don't get too comfy,

280
00:09:56,330 --> 00:09:58,024
'cause it's all going back.

281
00:09:59,271 --> 00:10:02,121
You know, that kind of attitude
is why I moved out! (Door closes)

282
00:10:02,819 --> 00:10:05,809
<i>So while Axl was enjoying</i>
<i>his uncle's stolen furniture,</i>

283
00:10:05,944 --> 00:10:08,120
<i>Mike was busy</i>
<i>trying to return it.</i>

284
00:10:08,296 --> 00:10:09,597
What is this?

285
00:10:09,981 --> 00:10:11,642
How are you gonna
take the furniture back

286
00:10:11,749 --> 00:10:12,900
in that clown car?

287
00:10:13,023 --> 00:10:14,886
Oh, I think
if you stack it right...

288
00:10:15,006 --> 00:10:15,940
Damn it, Rusty!

289
00:10:16,063 --> 00:10:18,099
You can't keep doing this!
Enough!

290
00:10:18,265 --> 00:10:19,537
You're driving me crazy!

291
00:10:19,642 --> 00:10:22,307
You're irresponsible,
unreliable.

292
00:10:22,420 --> 00:10:23,717
You're possibly a felon!

293
00:10:23,836 --> 00:10:26,363
Hey, hey, hey. I think
you're being unreasonable.

294
00:10:26,495 --> 00:10:28,476
I spent the whole morning
rounding this car up,

295
00:10:28,636 --> 00:10:30,176
putting $2 of gas in it,

296
00:10:30,338 --> 00:10:32,293
which I'm not even
gonna charge you for.

297
00:10:33,246 --> 00:10:35,099
A "thank you" might be nice.

298
00:10:38,166 --> 00:10:40,355
Okay, Sue, time to
shut down the cookie factory

299
00:10:40,470 --> 00:10:42,458
I gotta rummage through
the fridge for dinner.

300
00:10:42,598 --> 00:10:44,535
Oh, that's okay.
We already have dinner plans.

301
00:10:44,649 --> 00:10:45,958
Yeah, we're going
over to Axl's.

302
00:10:46,708 --> 00:10:48,747
Should never go over to
somebody's house empty-handed.

303
00:10:50,477 --> 00:10:51,781
I'm done.

304
00:10:52,292 --> 00:10:53,349
- What do you mean?
- I'm done.

305
00:10:53,479 --> 00:10:54,807
I'm done with my brother.
It's over.

306
00:10:54,924 --> 00:10:56,310
I told him not to come
for Christmas.

307
00:10:57,011 --> 00:10:58,031
Wow. You did?

308
00:10:58,172 --> 00:11:00,182
If he were a friend, I'd have
been done with him years ago!

309
00:11:00,325 --> 00:11:01,698
I get nothing out of it
but headaches!

310
00:11:01,800 --> 00:11:03,558
And I don't want to hear
"you do for family," Frankie.

311
00:11:03,730 --> 00:11:05,459
I did enough for him.
I'm done.

312
00:11:07,114 --> 00:11:08,434
Okay, then.

313
00:11:08,919 --> 00:11:10,127
Okay.

314
00:11:19,995 --> 00:11:20,897
Oh, no.

315
00:11:21,008 --> 00:11:22,888
I forgot about cookies
for Christmas dinner!

316
00:11:23,020 --> 00:11:24,024
How many people are coming?

317
00:11:24,143 --> 00:11:25,339
Are grandpa
and Uncle Rusty coming?

318
00:11:25,523 --> 00:11:28,335
Whoever's comin' is comin'.
Whoever isn't, isn't. (Bottles clank)

319
00:11:29,240 --> 00:11:30,213
(Mouths words)
(Refrigerator door closes)

320
00:11:30,328 --> 00:11:32,526
Well, I'm not
wise man number two anymore.

321
00:11:32,717 --> 00:11:34,290
Oh, Brick.

322
00:11:34,408 --> 00:11:36,759
I'm wise man number two
<i>and</i> number three.

323
00:11:36,884 --> 00:11:39,306
Turns out wise man three
has a bit of a shoving problem.

324
00:11:39,443 --> 00:11:41,074
So my new line is,

325
00:11:41,203 --> 00:11:43,771
"I bring you frankincense,
and he brings you myrrh."

326
00:11:43,891 --> 00:11:45,867
Wow, Brick, that's great!

327
00:11:46,039 --> 00:11:47,645
Two parts.

328
00:11:47,775 --> 00:11:49,823
They must think you're
doing a really great job.

329
00:11:49,942 --> 00:11:51,870
<i>And</i> you get to say "myrrh"
like you wanted.

330
00:11:51,996 --> 00:11:54,180
When you got it, you got it.

331
00:11:54,333 --> 00:11:55,447
What do you got there?

332
00:11:56,063 --> 00:11:58,483
Oh, it's the invitation
to Axl's Christmas party.

333
00:11:59,696 --> 00:12:01,262
Didn't you get one?

334
00:12:02,129 --> 00:12:03,199
Hmm.

335
00:12:03,326 --> 00:12:04,723
Awkward.

336
00:12:07,441 --> 00:12:08,727
Hey.

337
00:12:09,616 --> 00:12:12,208
Where the hell's
my Christmas tree?

338
00:12:13,531 --> 00:12:15,075
(Sighs deeply)

339
00:12:15,824 --> 00:12:18,090
<i>(Jazz version of "Angels We</i>
<i>Have Heard On High" playing)</i>

340
00:12:18,202 --> 00:12:20,105
<i>Well, Axl was certainly</i>
<i>prepared for Christmas,</i>

341
00:12:20,297 --> 00:12:22,722
<i>and with ten days</i>
<i>until my discount kicked in,</i>

342
00:12:22,866 --> 00:12:24,757
<i>I was preparing in my own way.</i>
(Clink)

343
00:12:24,865 --> 00:12:27,099
(Choir) ♪ deck the halls with
boughs of holly ♪ (Clinking)

344
00:12:27,222 --> 00:12:29,858
♪ Fa la la la la la la la la ♪

345
00:12:29,990 --> 00:12:32,956
- Hey.
- Hey! (Laughs)

346
00:12:33,274 --> 00:12:35,262
♪ Fa la la la la la la la la ♪

347
00:12:35,406 --> 00:12:37,996
♪ don we now our gay apparel ♪

348
00:12:38,120 --> 00:12:38,919
♪ fa la la ♪

349
00:12:39,033 --> 00:12:40,615
<i>♪ la la la la la la ♪</i>

350
00:12:40,777 --> 00:12:43,591
I swear you would not believe
the lengths customers go to

351
00:12:43,699 --> 00:12:46,779
to hide stuff so they can buy it
later when the sales kick in.

352
00:12:46,892 --> 00:12:48,606
Oh, no. I can believe it.
(Forced chuckle)

353
00:12:48,742 --> 00:12:51,308
<i>♪</i>

354
00:12:53,191 --> 00:12:54,164
(Sighs)

355
00:12:54,277 --> 00:12:56,295
Okay, now what
are we gonna do tomorrow?

356
00:12:56,435 --> 00:12:59,265
(Children) Rock it for Jesus!

357
00:12:59,387 --> 00:13:00,844
Okay.

358
00:13:01,769 --> 00:13:03,148
(Mike exhales)

359
00:13:04,154 --> 00:13:05,803
Brick, it's been a long day.
Let's go.

360
00:13:05,933 --> 00:13:07,036
Okay, one second.

361
00:13:07,142 --> 00:13:08,889
I need to get fitted
for my crown.

362
00:13:09,010 --> 00:13:10,335
Brick.

363
00:13:10,624 --> 00:13:11,935
(Sighs)

364
00:13:14,136 --> 00:13:15,307
(Boy in distance) Bye!

365
00:13:15,814 --> 00:13:17,106
(Door closes)

366
00:13:18,099 --> 00:13:19,058
Mm.

367
00:13:19,178 --> 00:13:20,815
Holidays can be
a stressful time.

368
00:13:20,934 --> 00:13:22,010
So I hear.

369
00:13:22,126 --> 00:13:23,786
You know, Mike, I get the sense

370
00:13:23,904 --> 00:13:25,322
that something's
weighing on your mind.

371
00:13:25,484 --> 00:13:27,493
You know,
I'm a pretty good listener.

372
00:13:27,606 --> 00:13:28,818
No. I'm good.

373
00:13:28,938 --> 00:13:32,209
- Dealing with family
can be tough. - Mm.

374
00:13:32,420 --> 00:13:34,774
Oh, yeah? I hadn't
really thought about it.

375
00:13:34,885 --> 00:13:37,190
But you know, you don't have to do it alone.
(Plays chords)

376
00:13:37,314 --> 00:13:38,390
Alone's fine.

377
00:13:38,517 --> 00:13:40,170
I'm talking 'bout
kickin' it upstairs

378
00:13:40,279 --> 00:13:41,965
to a different department.

379
00:13:42,093 --> 00:13:45,829
♪ Talk to the man upstairs ♪

380
00:13:46,068 --> 00:13:49,831
♪ he'll listen
to your prayers ♪

381
00:13:50,368 --> 00:13:52,794
- ♪ 'stead of just sayin' grace ♪
- How--

382
00:13:52,920 --> 00:13:54,667
♪ before you stuff your face ♪

383
00:13:54,874 --> 00:13:57,574
♪ talk to the man upstairs ♪

384
00:13:57,677 --> 00:13:58,676
♪ try a prayer ♪

385
00:13:58,836 --> 00:14:01,039
All lines open 24/7.

386
00:14:01,149 --> 00:14:02,838
(Plays flourish)

387
00:14:02,953 --> 00:14:04,357
Okay. Yeah.

388
00:14:04,502 --> 00:14:06,602
Thanks, but the Colts
are rebuilding,

389
00:14:06,727 --> 00:14:08,381
and I don't want to
distract him from that.

390
00:14:08,532 --> 00:14:10,847
You know,
he's a pretty good multitasker.

391
00:14:10,967 --> 00:14:12,965
I bet he could handle
you and the Colts.

392
00:14:13,087 --> 00:14:15,152
Just something
to think about, Mike.

393
00:14:15,276 --> 00:14:17,023
Will do. Brick!

394
00:14:19,165 --> 00:14:20,838
I'm just gonna go get him.

395
00:14:21,373 --> 00:14:22,373
Sure.

396
00:14:23,745 --> 00:14:25,652
<i>So the end of my 20th day</i>
<i>had finally come,</i>

397
00:14:25,768 --> 00:14:27,387
<i>and my discount was kicking in.</i>

398
00:14:27,515 --> 00:14:29,382
<i>All I had to do</i>
<i>was make it to closing</i>

399
00:14:29,511 --> 00:14:32,225
<i>cash out, and hightail it</i>
<i>to Brick's play.</i>

400
00:14:32,426 --> 00:14:34,675
Look at this.
Found another stash.

401
00:14:34,858 --> 00:14:36,104
And I don't even wanna tell you

402
00:14:36,221 --> 00:14:39,046
- what I just pulled out of a
mannequin's underpants. - Ooh.

403
00:14:39,256 --> 00:14:40,926
Legally, I can't resell it.

404
00:14:41,066 --> 00:14:44,355
You know what? Let me put
that stuff back for you, Penny.

405
00:14:44,464 --> 00:14:45,962
You've been working
so hard all week.

406
00:14:46,092 --> 00:14:48,419
Aw, thanks, Frankie.

407
00:14:48,535 --> 00:14:49,987
Oh, you're a real go-getter.

408
00:14:50,094 --> 00:14:51,802
Well, I wasn't fishing
for that compliment,

409
00:14:51,939 --> 00:14:53,156
but I'll reel it in.

410
00:14:53,264 --> 00:14:54,556
(Laughs) Reel...

411
00:14:54,691 --> 00:14:58,903
<i>(Instrumental</i>
<i>"Up On The Housetop" playing)</i>

412
00:15:01,804 --> 00:15:03,572
(Gasps) Sweet.

413
00:15:04,734 --> 00:15:08,300
<i>♪</i>

414
00:15:14,873 --> 00:15:17,832
(Gasps) Oh, come on!

415
00:15:18,849 --> 00:15:20,959
♪ ♪

416
00:15:27,303 --> 00:15:28,726
Eye. Eye. Beard.

417
00:15:28,860 --> 00:15:30,388
Eye. Eye. Beard.

418
00:15:30,517 --> 00:15:32,087
Eye. Eye. Cramp!

419
00:15:32,267 --> 00:15:34,737
Oh, God! Aah! Hand cramp!

420
00:15:34,855 --> 00:15:36,752
No! Not now! Not now!

421
00:15:36,878 --> 00:15:38,139
Come on, Sue, hurry it up.

422
00:15:38,257 --> 00:15:39,727
We're gonna be late
for your brother's play.

423
00:15:39,873 --> 00:15:42,725
Oh, no! Aah!

424
00:15:42,857 --> 00:15:44,456
I've been robbed!

425
00:15:44,581 --> 00:15:46,024
What happened
to all my cool stuff?

426
00:15:46,133 --> 00:15:47,239
It wasn't your stuff.

427
00:15:47,356 --> 00:15:49,409
I got a couple guys
and a truck from the quarry,

428
00:15:49,540 --> 00:15:50,420
and I took it all back.

429
00:15:50,551 --> 00:15:52,322
So where am I
supposed to live now?

430
00:15:52,475 --> 00:15:54,699
- How about in your room?
- I can't go back to that dump

431
00:15:54,844 --> 00:15:56,582
after living in the garage.
Are you crazy?

432
00:15:56,733 --> 00:15:58,736
I need my sick crib!

433
00:15:58,915 --> 00:16:00,248
Ugh! Pfft.

434
00:16:04,234 --> 00:16:05,130
(Door closes)

435
00:16:06,364 --> 00:16:07,408
(Object scrapes)

436
00:16:08,792 --> 00:16:09,967
(Clicks)

437
00:16:14,416 --> 00:16:16,159
(Sighs)

438
00:16:16,601 --> 00:16:18,003
Mm.

439
00:16:23,541 --> 00:16:24,748
(Sighs)

440
00:16:25,104 --> 00:16:27,893
So, uh, my brother...

441
00:16:29,673 --> 00:16:32,653
I mean... well, you saw.
You're probably up to speed.

442
00:16:32,774 --> 00:16:35,737
I'm just wondering
if I did the right thing.

443
00:16:37,230 --> 00:16:40,025
I-I don't know if you
show me, or...

444
00:16:41,483 --> 00:16:42,981
if that's even the way it works.

445
00:16:43,134 --> 00:16:44,364
Frankie's more
the church person.

446
00:16:44,483 --> 00:16:47,001
If you told <i>her</i>
and she told me,

447
00:16:47,122 --> 00:16:48,401
that'd be fine.

448
00:16:53,568 --> 00:16:54,919
(Sighs)

449
00:16:55,036 --> 00:16:57,615
Anyway, thanks for Andrew Luck.

450
00:16:59,877 --> 00:17:02,102
Cookies!
Get your Santa cookies.

451
00:17:02,330 --> 00:17:03,802
Once they're gone,
they're gone.

452
00:17:07,194 --> 00:17:09,071
If everyone could please
grab a seat,

453
00:17:09,182 --> 00:17:11,968
"JC's Rockin' Birthday Jam"
is about to begin.

454
00:17:12,090 --> 00:17:13,510
The kids have been
working real hard.

455
00:17:13,636 --> 00:17:17,494
So sit back, enjoy the show.
Thanks for coming down.

456
00:17:18,606 --> 00:17:19,537
(Exhales)

457
00:17:19,648 --> 00:17:20,820
(Lowered voice) Where were you?
Why are you so late?

458
00:17:20,929 --> 00:17:22,114
(Lowered voice)
I was hiding presents

459
00:17:22,232 --> 00:17:23,253
on this really high shelf

460
00:17:23,360 --> 00:17:25,228
so nobody would
buy them out from under me.

461
00:17:25,386 --> 00:17:27,095
- Smart.
- I know, right?

462
00:17:27,231 --> 00:17:28,871
Until somebody
wheeled my ladder away

463
00:17:28,988 --> 00:17:30,231
and I got stuck up there.

464
00:17:30,348 --> 00:17:32,044
By the time I got down,
the store was closed,

465
00:17:32,159 --> 00:17:32,998
the manager was gone,

466
00:17:33,110 --> 00:17:34,645
and I had to roll
under the gate.

467
00:17:35,075 --> 00:17:36,338
So you didn't get any presents?

468
00:17:36,456 --> 00:17:38,445
No. Zip. Zero presents.

469
00:17:38,558 --> 00:17:39,643
But tomorrow's Christmas.

470
00:17:39,754 --> 00:17:41,373
Oh, really, Mike?
I did not know that.

471
00:17:42,180 --> 00:17:42,820
♪

472
00:17:42,947 --> 00:17:45,503
♪ the angel told Mary,
"a baby you will carry ♪

473
00:17:45,642 --> 00:17:48,361
♪ Joseph, don't bother
'cause you got a high father" ♪

474
00:17:48,490 --> 00:17:50,198
<i>So it was Christmas Eve,</i>

475
00:17:50,315 --> 00:17:52,149
<i>and none of us</i>
<i>were in the spirit.</i>

476
00:17:52,269 --> 00:17:54,756
<i>And Brick's performance</i>
<i>wasn't making it any better.</i>

477
00:17:54,927 --> 00:17:56,514
(Shoes squeaking) ♪ 'cause
you got a high father ♪

478
00:17:56,633 --> 00:17:57,700
♪ and I know it sounds odd ♪

479
00:17:57,830 --> 00:17:59,572
- What's he doing?
- I don't know.

480
00:17:59,939 --> 00:18:01,575
♪ To avoid a misconception ♪
(Squeaking continues)

481
00:18:01,695 --> 00:18:03,164
♪ It's immaculate conception ♪

482
00:18:03,328 --> 00:18:05,914
There it is,
the star in the east.

483
00:18:06,059 --> 00:18:07,739
It will lead us
to the new king.

484
00:18:07,964 --> 00:18:10,464
(Squeaking continues)

485
00:18:10,586 --> 00:18:12,484
(Audience laughing)

486
00:18:14,177 --> 00:18:16,829
So we shall take
our son to Egypt

487
00:18:16,956 --> 00:18:19,760
and save him
from Herod's wrath.

488
00:18:19,933 --> 00:18:21,852
You didn't do that right.

489
00:18:21,980 --> 00:18:24,306
It's kind of a big moment,
and you didn't sell it.

490
00:18:24,436 --> 00:18:25,879
Now he's a director.

491
00:18:25,968 --> 00:18:27,056
(Laughs) (Laughs)

492
00:18:27,155 --> 00:18:28,247
I bring you gold.

493
00:18:28,454 --> 00:18:30,266
(Box squeaking)

494
00:18:30,416 --> 00:18:31,493
(Whispers) Brick!

495
00:18:31,616 --> 00:18:33,125
I bring you gold.

496
00:18:33,285 --> 00:18:34,314
(Squeaking continues)

497
00:18:34,432 --> 00:18:36,197
(Both mouthing words)

498
00:18:36,301 --> 00:18:37,222
I bring you gold,

499
00:18:37,368 --> 00:18:40,827
he brings you frankincense,
and he brings you myrrh!

500
00:18:40,959 --> 00:18:42,467
(Stifling laugh)

501
00:18:44,096 --> 00:18:45,588
What's he doing now?

502
00:18:45,716 --> 00:18:46,764
He's looking up.

503
00:18:46,891 --> 00:18:48,981
- ♪ Three wise men... ♪
- Now he's looking down.

504
00:18:49,104 --> 00:18:50,584
(Laughs)
He's twirling his crown.

505
00:18:50,716 --> 00:18:52,636
(Gasps)
Oh! He's eating a cookie.

506
00:18:52,755 --> 00:18:53,672
One of mine?

507
00:18:53,769 --> 00:18:55,330
<i>Well, sometimes people</i>
<i>surprise you,</i>

508
00:18:55,455 --> 00:18:57,044
<i>and sometimes they don't.</i>

509
00:18:57,213 --> 00:19:01,040
<i>Sometimes, they act exactly</i>
<i>the way you expect them to.</i>

510
00:19:01,467 --> 00:19:04,401
(Sue and Frankie laughing)

511
00:19:06,116 --> 00:19:08,343
I guess we won't be moving
to Hollywood anytime soon.

512
00:19:08,472 --> 00:19:10,347
No, I don't think so.

513
00:19:10,900 --> 00:19:12,475
(Laughs)

514
00:19:13,733 --> 00:19:17,968
These are the actual cookies
eaten by a wise man on stage.

515
00:19:18,095 --> 00:19:19,270
Hey, Sue Heck.

516
00:19:19,392 --> 00:19:21,338
Terrific job
on the concession stand.

517
00:19:21,460 --> 00:19:24,434
No. I failed.
But it's okay.

518
00:19:24,552 --> 00:19:26,320
You know, you can tell me.
I can take it.

519
00:19:26,437 --> 00:19:28,670
Well, probably not,
so I would go easy on me.

520
00:19:28,789 --> 00:19:30,751
You don't fail
when you do your best.

521
00:19:30,876 --> 00:19:32,611
Anyway, I'm headed
up to Bloomington.

522
00:19:32,763 --> 00:19:35,832
They have this big interfaith
snowball fight on campus

523
00:19:35,954 --> 00:19:38,240
where they work out
thousands of years of conflict

524
00:19:38,361 --> 00:19:39,981
in a fun, safe environment.

525
00:19:40,140 --> 00:19:43,263
Would it be cool if I took
some of your delicious cookies?

526
00:19:43,646 --> 00:19:45,516
Yes. (Laughs)

527
00:19:45,767 --> 00:19:47,183
I just wish
there was more of 'em.

528
00:19:47,356 --> 00:19:50,473
Oh, well, I have
a thousand more in the car.

529
00:19:50,612 --> 00:19:53,071
I mean that. A thousand.

530
00:19:54,734 --> 00:19:55,796
(Crunches)

531
00:19:55,925 --> 00:19:58,552
Brick! Hey.

532
00:19:59,301 --> 00:20:00,470
So what happened?

533
00:20:00,585 --> 00:20:02,571
You seemed a little
distracted up there.

534
00:20:02,690 --> 00:20:03,575
Really?

535
00:20:03,729 --> 00:20:04,836
- Mm.
- Yeah.

536
00:20:04,972 --> 00:20:07,073
For the whole second half,
you faced the back of the stage.

537
00:20:07,209 --> 00:20:09,292
Hmm. Well,
I gave it a whack.

538
00:20:09,538 --> 00:20:10,511
(Whispers) Whack.

539
00:20:10,706 --> 00:20:11,694
(High-pitched voice)
Whoop.

540
00:20:11,851 --> 00:20:13,959
(Laughs)
Dude, that was awesome.

541
00:20:14,102 --> 00:20:15,678
(Laughs) This thing was
a total suck-fest

542
00:20:15,800 --> 00:20:16,974
till you showed up, seriously.

543
00:20:17,132 --> 00:20:19,572
You rocked it. That
shoe-squeaking was hilarious.

544
00:20:19,695 --> 00:20:21,553
Thanks.
I saw it on a TV show

545
00:20:21,682 --> 00:20:24,084
where guys in shiny shorts
ran up and down a floor,

546
00:20:24,230 --> 00:20:26,824
and I really liked
the squeaking sound.

547
00:20:26,977 --> 00:20:28,940
Brick, that was
a basketball game. (Chuckles)

548
00:20:29,065 --> 00:20:30,771
Yeah, it was. Up top.

549
00:20:30,906 --> 00:20:33,382
(Laughs) Come on.
One more. Is that all you got?

550
00:20:33,528 --> 00:20:35,215
Whoop. Nope. Not this time.

551
00:20:35,393 --> 00:20:38,287
No-- oh. It's okay, one more.
No! Sorry.

552
00:20:38,423 --> 00:20:40,855
<i>And at that moment,</i>
<i>Mike realized--</i>

553
00:20:41,026 --> 00:20:43,185
<i>Brick was Axl's weird brother.</i>

554
00:20:43,424 --> 00:20:46,497
<i>And it'd kill him if he ever</i>
<i>thought there would come a day</i>

555
00:20:46,605 --> 00:20:49,395
<i>when they would stop</i>
<i>speaking to each other.</i>

556
00:20:50,797 --> 00:20:53,570
(Sighs) I'm telling you, man,
it's a golden opportunity.

557
00:20:53,689 --> 00:20:54,892
I don't know, Rusty.

558
00:20:55,005 --> 00:20:57,387
Come on, Mike, how many llamas
can I put you down for?

559
00:20:57,514 --> 00:21:00,192
(Paper crackling)

560
00:21:02,127 --> 00:21:02,964
- What is this?
- Mom?

561
00:21:03,079 --> 00:21:03,897
Is this a joke?

562
00:21:04,003 --> 00:21:06,412
Okay, those are from
the JJ Macky Christmas mailer,

563
00:21:06,537 --> 00:21:08,818
and they represent
presents to come.

564
00:21:08,953 --> 00:21:11,442
(Gasps) A Camaro? Awesome!

565
00:21:11,589 --> 00:21:13,159
Uh, turn it around.

566
00:21:14,507 --> 00:21:16,128
A shirt?

567
00:21:17,142 --> 00:21:18,867
<i>So Mike and Rusty made up.</i>

568
00:21:19,000 --> 00:21:20,141
<i>It wasn't that hard,</i>

569
00:21:20,248 --> 00:21:22,856
<i>'cause Rusty hadn't realized</i>
<i>they were even in a fight.</i>

570
00:21:23,008 --> 00:21:25,732
<i>And I made up for Christmas day</i>
<i>the day after Christmas,</i>

571
00:21:25,875 --> 00:21:29,460
<i>with 50% off</i>
<i>plus my employee discount.</i>

572
00:21:29,996 --> 00:21:32,208
<i>Yep, the Heck family</i>
<i>cleaned up.</i>

573
00:21:32,557 --> 00:21:34,930
<i>I think we may have</i>
<i>a new family tradition.</i>

